---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '~/components/Breadcrumb.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Chains — The Deterministic Engine | Kefiw"
  description="Chained calculator pipelines. Each stage's output becomes the next stage's input via a shared session context. Closed-form math, connected."
  canonical="/chains/"
  keywords={['chained calculators', 'life path calculator', 'financial survival pipeline', 'deterministic engine']}
>
  <Breadcrumb crumbs={[{ href: '/', label: 'Home' }, { href: '/chains/', label: 'Chains' }]} />
  <article class="container-wide py-6">
    <header class="mb-8 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-cyan-600">The Deterministic Engine</p>
      <h1 class="mt-1 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Chains</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-slate-700">
        A chain is a pipeline: multiple calculators wired to a shared session context. Change an
        upstream input, watch every downstream number move. Same deterministic math — connected.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
        Treat data as a stream, not a one-off. One data entry flows through to a final verdict.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <a
        href="/chains/survival-01/"
        class="block rounded-lg border border-cyan-200 bg-white p-5 transition hover:border-cyan-500 hover:bg-cyan-50"
      >
        <div class="text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-cyan-600">SURVIVAL-01</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">The Life-Path Pipeline</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Subscription Purge → Gig-Net Floor → Runway Zero. Cut hidden leaks, size a real side-hustle,
          and watch your bankruptcy date move in real time.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-slate-500">3 stages · live variables · ~2 min to complete</div>
      </a>

      <a
        href="/chains/pivot-02/"
        class="block rounded-lg border border-cyan-200 bg-white p-5 transition hover:border-cyan-500 hover:bg-cyan-50"
      >
        <div class="text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-cyan-600">PIVOT-02</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Entrepreneurial Transition</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Minimum Viable Rate → Gig-Net Floor → Runway Zero. Price the corporate salary you left, check
          what the gig actually pays, project the runway the pivot buys.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-slate-500">3 stages · live variables · ~2 min to complete</div>
      </a>

      <a
        href="/chains/move-03/"
        class="block rounded-lg border border-cyan-200 bg-white p-5 transition hover:border-cyan-500 hover:bg-cyan-50"
      >
        <div class="text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-cyan-600">MOVE-03</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Geographic Relocation</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Geo Arbitrage → Subscription Purge → Runway Zero. Size the here-vs-there surplus, reset the
          subscription stack, and see the Zero Date move.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-slate-500">3 stages · live variables · ~2 min to complete</div>
      </a>

      <a
        href="/chains/focus-04/"
        class="block rounded-lg border border-cyan-200 bg-white p-5 transition hover:border-cyan-500 hover:bg-cyan-50"
      >
        <div class="text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-cyan-600">FOCUS-04</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Cognitive Repair Day</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Task Switching Tax → Focus Horizon → Decision Fatigue. Measure context overhead, focus decay,
          and willpower reserves — three closed-form models, one cascade.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-slate-500">3 stages · live variables · ~2 min to complete</div>
      </a>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-5">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">How chains work</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
        Every chain stage writes its primary output to a shared JSON object in your browser
        (<code class="rounded bg-white px-1 text-xs text-slate-800">kfw-session-context</code>).
        Downstream stages subscribe to relevant keys and re-hydrate live. Inputs stay local to your device —
        nothing is sent to a server.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
